de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.service.persistence

Class AHContactUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fraunhofer.fokus.oefit.adhoc.service.persistence.AHContactUtil

  • public class AHContactUtil
extends Object
    The persistence utility for the a h contact service. This utility wraps AHContactPersistenceImpl and provides direct access to the database for CRUD operations. This utility should only be used by the service layer, as it must operate within a transaction. Never access this utility in a JSP, controller, model, or other front-end class.

    Caching information and settings can be found in portal.properties

    Author:
    Brian Wing Shun Chan
    See Also:
    AHContactPersistence, AHContactPersistenceImpl

      • findByemail

        public static List<AHContact> findByemail(String email,
                          int start,
                          int end)
                                   throws com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException
        Returns a range of all the a h contacts where email = ?.

        Useful when paginating results. Returns a maximum of end - start instances. start and end are not primary keys, they are indexes in the result set. Thus, 0 refers to the first result in the set. Setting both start and end to QueryUtil.ALL_POS will return the full result set. If orderByComparator is specified, then the query will include the given ORDER BY logic. If orderByComparator is absent and pagination is required (start and end are not QueryUtil.ALL_POS), then the query will include the default ORDER BY logic from AHContactModelImpl. If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.

        Parameters:
        email - the email
        start - the lower bound of the range of a h contacts
        end - the upper bound of the range of a h contacts (not inclusive)
        Returns:
        the range of matching a h contacts
        Throws:
        com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException - if a system exception occurred

      • findAll

        public static List<AHContact> findAll(int start,
                      int end)
                               throws com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException
        Returns a range of all the a h contacts.

        Useful when paginating results. Returns a maximum of end - start instances. start and end are not primary keys, they are indexes in the result set. Thus, 0 refers to the first result in the set. Setting both start and end to QueryUtil.ALL_POS will return the full result set. If orderByComparator is specified, then the query will include the given ORDER BY logic. If orderByComparator is absent and pagination is required (start and end are not QueryUtil.ALL_POS), then the query will include the default ORDER BY logic from AHContactModelImpl. If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.

        Parameters:
        start - the lower bound of the range of a h contacts
        end - the upper bound of the range of a h contacts (not inclusive)
        Returns:
        the range of a h contacts
        Throws:
        com.liferay.portal.kernel.exception.SystemException - if a system exception occurred

If orderByComparator is specified, then the query will include the given ORDER BY logic. If orderByComparator is absent and pagination is required (start and end are not QueryUtil.ALL_POS), then the query will include the default ORDER BY logic from AHContactModelImpl. If both orderByComparator and pagination are absent, for performance reasons, the query will not have an ORDER BY clause and the returned result set will be sorted on by the primary key in an ascending order.
